So I'm reading through Acid Rain: Drizzle, by STRONG, and there are a lot of problems with it. Keep in mind I mean no disrespect to his other work, the amount he's contributed over the years speaks for itself. The original Acid Rain is one of my favorite stories.
The grammar is a big issue with the work. Random capitalization errors are present. One or two questions don't have question marks. The quotation marks are placed incorrectly in a lot of areas, making it confusing to discern the dialogue and the narrative.
I get that using all-caps for shouting is stylistic thing, but it draws attention to the fact that the dialogue is already weak, even for porn. There's no subtlety or depth to any thing that the characters are saying, I get that part of this is the fact that Star is juvenile in her behavior but even then I can't believe anyone talks this way in real life. This excerpt kind of speaks for itself.
>"OK OK! GO! if you go fast you might get a treat!" She says with more excitement than necessary.
>You look at her questioningly.
>"Treat?"
>Star pulls her shirt up revealing her grapefruit sized breasts.
>"YOU GET THESE!" She says as she hops slightly before quickly lowering her shirt "NOW GO!".
The narrative can use a lot of trimming. There's over-reliance on adverbs, and the physical desciption is clunky in many places. He describes tits as "fleshy orbs" during the sex scene, and between that and everything else I really don't know how anyone can keep masturbating to this. It's gratuitous in a bad way.
The whole thing reads like it wasn't proofread.
